<P>
REINER WARNS ABOUT ROOFING RIP-OFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dist. Atty. Ira Reiner warned Thursday that the recent rainfall and the winter 
season will probably result in an increase in roofing repair scams. 
</P>
<P>
Reiner issued his warning in the wake of the arrest earlier this week of Al Tom 
Nelson, 36, of Temple City, for allegedly bilking a Monrovia man out of $700 by 
spraying commercial roofing tar diluted with gasoline on the man's roof. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson pleaded innocent in Monrovia Municipal Court on Wednesday to one count 
of grand theft and remains in custody in lieu of $100,000 bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
