<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SPRING VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Spring Valley man already charged with killing a former Los Angeles Rams 
football player during an attempted robbery in La Mesa was charged Thursday 
with a second murder. 
</P>
<P>
George Ray Cunnington, 27, pleaded not guilty to the new charge of killing 
Robert Hetmer, 51, of Spring Valley several hours before the Nov. 18 slaying of 
Rey Nicholas Phillinganes, 23. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Steve Robinson told the court that his office is considering 
filing special-circumstances allegations, which could lead to the death penalty 
for Cunnington if he is convicted. The grounds for the special circumstances 
would be that multiple victims were killed and that the Phillinganes slaying 
occurred during an attempted robbery. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Municipal Judge Charles Patrick ordered bail to remain at $1 million. 
A preliminary hearing was set for March 31. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson said Cunnington had lived with Hetmer for several weeks before the 
shooting. He said the house was ransacked. 
</P>
<P>
Phillinganes was in his car when a gunman approached him, tapped on the window 
with the gun and then shot him in the chest. 
</P>
