<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA FREEWAY RAMPS TO CLOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several Ventura Freeway on- and off-ramps will be closed this weekend for 
repairs, according to the California Department of Transportation. 
</P>
<P>
From 9 p.m. Friday to 5:30 a.m. Monday, Caltrans will close the Winnetka Avenue 
eastbound off-ramp and westbound on-ramp, Canoga Avenue westbound off-ramp and 
eastbound on-ramp, and the Topanga Canyon Boulevard westbound on-ramp at 
Burbank Boulevard. The far right lanes of Winnetka and Canoga avenues and 
Topanga Canyon Boulevard near the ramps will also be closed. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans will pave, paint road stripes and replace guardrails on the ramps. 
</P>
<P>
The work is part of the ongoing Ventura Improvement Project, to expand and 
repair the Ventura Freeway from Calabasas to the Hollywood Freeway. Various 
ramps between Tampa Avenue and Valley Circle Boulevard will be closed during 
the next several weekends. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans' 24-hour toll-free hotline, 1-800-CALL VIP, has updated recorded 
information on ramp and road closures. 
</P>
