<P>
BELL-JEFF PRESS FLATTENS CHAMINADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS J. PARKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Employing a full-court press that forced 39 turnovers -- including 15 in a 
7-minute span -- the Bell-Jeff High girls' basketball team beat Chaminade, 
60-35, in a San Fernando Valley League game at Chaminade on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
After the Eagles' Judy Galido made a layup to cut Bell-Jeff's lead to 5 points 
early in the third quarter, the Guards forced Chaminade turnovers on 15 of the 
Eagles' next 17 possessions. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff (14-0, 3-0 in league play) scored 17 consecutive points, including a 
trio of 3-point baskets by guard Lisa Negrete, who finished with 18 points. 
Negrete's long-range shooting also opened up the middle for forward Andja 
Vucurevic, who scored a game-high 23 points, including 15 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore forward Pamela Powers led Chaminade with 10 points. Galido added 8 
points and 15 rebounds. CHRIS J. PARKER 
