<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTSCOPE; 
</P>
<P>
JUNIOR KINGS WIN AGAIN IN ICE HOCKEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Junior Kings, a Pee Wee level (12-13 years) ice hockey team from Southern 
California, went undefeated and won an international tournament in Bemidji, 
Minn. Leon Rodriguez, Richard Park and Jamie Hanford from Rancho Palos Verdes 
helped the Kings sweep to a 4-0 record. The team is sponsored by the National 
Hockey League Los Angeles Kings. The Junior Kings have won three major youth 
tournaments this season. In February the team will compete in an international 
event in Quebec. 
</P>
<P>
Cathy Hanlon Marino, a player on the Ladies Professional Golf Assn. tour, was 
inducted into the Palos Verdes Golf Club Hall of Fame. She joins previous 
inductees Bud Oakley, John Richarson and Mark Pfeil. Marino has averaged 
$70,000 a year in winnings on the circuit and holds the women's course record 
(71) at Palos Verdes Golf Club. 
</P>
