<TEXT>
<P>
Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell to the lowest level since 
November. The Treasury Department sold $9 billion of the bills at an average 
discount rate of 8.45%, down from 8.49% at the last auction Dec. 15. The rates 
were the lowest since Nov. 17, when the one-year bills sold for 7.92%. The new 
discount rate understates the actual return to investors -- 9.16% with a 
$10,000 bill selling for $9,145.60. 
</P>
</TEXT>
