<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CANADIENS MASTER BRUINS, 5-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Montreal Canadiens, who were eliminated by the Boston Bruins from the 
Stanley Cup playoffs last spring, are making up for it this season. 
</P>
<P>
The Canadiens improved their season record to 6-0-1 against the Bruins with a 
5-3 victory at Boston Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
"The playoffs are something we'll remember if we meet them in the playoffs 
again this year," said Montreal veteran Mike McPhee, whose goal at the end of 
the second period killed a Boston rally. 
</P>
<P>
Montreal's Stephane Richer had 1 goal and 2 assists. 
</P>
<P>
Buffalo 6, Chicago 5 -- Ray Sheppard of the Sabres scored at 9:51 of the third 
period as the Blackhawks lost their 12th consecutive road game. 
</P>
<P>
Pittsburgh 9, Minnesota 2 -- Rob Brown scored a goal and assisted on 5 others, 
and Mario Lemieux had a goal and 3 assists to lead the Penguins to victory over 
the North Stars at Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
Philadelphia 7, Quebec 2 -- Ron Sutter had 2 goals and 2 assists, and Mike 
Bullard scored twice as the Flyers defeated the Nordiques at Philadelphia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
