<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pittsburgh-based Allegheny International announced plans to cancel a merger 
agreement with Donaldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette, a New York securities firm, in 
favor of a deal to sell its core Oster-Sunbeam division to Towson, Md.-based 
Black &amp; Decker Corp. for $260 million. The proposed sale is the centerpiece 
of an independent plan of reorganization that management intends to present in 
bankruptcy court, where creditors had backed the proposal from the securities 
firm. The Oster-Sunbeam division makes a range of small household appliances, 
including shavers, mixers and other kitchen appliances. 
