<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BUSINESSMAN FINED FOR SEX HARASSMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Thomas, a public housing landlord and investor in fast-food 
restaurants, has been fined by the California Fair Employment and Housing 
Commission for sexually harassing a receptionist in his Los Angeles office. 
</P>
<P>
The commission found Thomas liable for harassing the receptionist, who quit her 
job the day after the Jan. 30, 1985, incident. In testimony before the 
commission, the receptionist said Thomas made sexual advances toward her when 
she went to his home to pick up a salary advance. 
</P>
<P>
The receptionist worked in the offices of Huncot Properties, which administers 
Section 8 public housing units in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The commission ordered Thomas to pay the receptionist $550 in back pay and 
$10,000 in compensatory damages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
