<P>
STORM DRAIN PROJECT TO AFFECT TRAFFIC FLOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The construction of a storm drain project on Chapman Avenue in Garden Grove is 
scheduled to begin in mid-January. The project is designed to relieve problems 
with standing water and flooding on Chapman from Gilbert Street through East 
Euclid Street. 
</P>
<P>
Work in these areas is expected to continue until July. Traffic flow and 
parking in the construction area will be restricted during the work. Efforts 
will be made to provide access to businesses and residents along the route. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call Mel Araki in Garden Grove engineering services at 
(714) 741-5181. 
