<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MARINA OVERTAKES EDISON WITH FOURTH-QUARTER RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marina High School overcame a 7-point fourth-quarter deficit to defeat Edison, 
49-41, in a Sunset League girls' basketball game Thursday at Marina. 
</P>
<P>
Edison led, 37-30, with 5 minutes 48 seconds remaining before Marina, led by 
junior guard Melisa Sortino, junior center Kristy Sparks and junior guard 
Christa Yorke, started a 19-4 run. 
</P>
<P>
During the spurt, Sortino scored 8 of her 13 points, Sparks had 5 of her 11 and 
Yorke 4 of her 10. Sparks also had 8 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Senior forward Krisden Tanabe scored 13 points and junior guard Debbie Fischer 
scored 11 for Edison (6-9 overall, 1-2 in league play). Marina is 15-3, 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 64, Westminster 11 -- Carolyn Fox scored 10 points, Kami 
Bigler, Amy Brand and Kathryn Kendall scored 8 each for visiting Fountain 
Valley (12-7, 2-1). Westminster (0-3 in league) didn't score in the second 
quarter and trailed, 35-4, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 58, Huntington Beach 25 -- Fabiola Nunez scored 11 points for 
visiting Ocean View (3-0 in league). 
</P>
<P>
In the Angelus League: 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei 71, St. Paul 45 -- Center Kelly O'Brien scored 20 points and grabbed 
13 rebounds, and guard Krisha Thompson added 19 points and 10 steals for 
visiting Mater Dei (12-5, 3-0). Forward Cori Martin added 16 points and 14 
rebounds for Mater Dei. Forward Shannon Gray scored 20 points and guard Colleen 
Jewell had 18 for St. Paul (0-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Valley 63, Santa Ana 40 -- Junior forward Francesca Rumps scored a 
game-high 28 points for visiting Santa Ana Valley (8-5, 2-1). Junior Nilda 
Valdez added 19 for Santa Ana Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 60, Villa Park 36 -- Senior forward Kerri Erkenbrack scored 20 points 
for visiting Canyon (12-4, 3-0). Junior center Evonne Caovertte scored 13 for 
Villa Park (4-9, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 58, El Modena 17 -- Center Tanya Foxe scored 17 points and had 9 
rebounds, and forward Sandi Rasmussen added 10 points to lead host Foothill 
(10-7, 3-0). Foothill had a 19-point lead at halftime and outscored El Modena, 
who dropped to 0-3 in league play, 16-0 in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Loara 46, Los Alamitos 34 -- Guard Melanie Sparks and forward Michelle Roland 
scored 12 points each and guard Kim Yoshioka added 10 points and 8 assists to 
lead Loara (12-7, 2-1) at Los Alamitos (1-2). Center Melinda Armstrong had 13 
points for Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Sonora 35, Troy 20 -- Lorene Rutisell scored 10 points and had 11 rebounds to 
lead host Sonora (4-9, 2-1). Sisters Monica and Thalia Polley each scored 8 for 
Sonora. Melissa Clevenger scored 8 for Troy. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 53, Orange Lutheran 48 -- Angela Garza scored 22 points and 
Cheri Culp added 14 to lead host Whittier Christian (5-0 in league). Pam Marty 
scored 14 points and Krista Whelply 12 for Orange Lutheran (6-5, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
Brethren 34, Capistrano Valley Christian 28 -- Carrie Shannon scored 15 for 
visiting Capistrano Valley Christian (3-8, 0-5 overall). Brethren is 1-4 in 
league. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 88, Magnolia 11 -- Forward Candy Anderson scored 20 points and grabbed 
13 rebounds to pace host Valencia (9-7, 1-1). Center Kristen McDonald added 15 
points, Fig Lo scored 14 and Nancy Amoroso 10 points for Valencia. Valencia 
opened a 49-8 halftime lead and held Magnolia (1-1) to 1 point in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Western 56, Anaheim 26 -- Vicki Evans scored 23 points and Jill Salazar scored 
16 for visiting Western (10-6, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Orange 54, Laguna Beach 39 -- Orange trailed, 25-23, at the half but outscored 
visiting Laguna Beach, 12-6, in the third quarter. Nicole Champion scored 21 
points and had 14 rebounds and Ginnie Hall had 15 points and 12 rebounds for 
Orange (8-6, 1-1), which switched to a full-court press in the second half. Liz 
Stall scored 23 for Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 53, Laguna Hills 20 -- Senior forward Lisa Wehren had 19 points and 
17 rebounds, and guard Leslie Rathbun contributed 12 points to pace Woodbridge 
(11-5, 2-0) at Laguna Hills (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
University 45, Saddleback 42 -- Sandy Johnson scored 4 points in the final 2 
minutes for visiting University (13-3, 2-0). Johnson had 5 points and 9 
rebounds. Noelle Sase had a game-high 15 points on 7-of-10 shooting for 
University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
