<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SUNNY HILLS EDGES SONORA ON GUGLER'S GOAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman Heidi Gugler scored to break a 1-1 tie and give Sunny Hills High 
School a 2-1 victory over Sonora in a Freeway League girls' soccer match 
Thursday at Sonora. 
</P>
<P>
Angela Macintosh had the other goal for Sunny Hills (8-3-1 overall, 2-1 in 
league play). Senior goalie Erica Gugler, Heidi's sister, had 11 saves. 
</P>
<P>
Tami Taber scored for Sonora (1-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 1, Kennedy 0 -- Sheryl Jones scored a second-half goal on an assist 
by Robin Karnes at Kennedy. Karnes' one-touch pass from 30 yards out allowed 
Jones to go 1-on-1 with the goalie and helped La Quinta improve to 8-2, 2-0. 
Wendy Wilson had 4 saves for the shutout. 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 6, Rancho Alamitos 1 -- Devon Fitzpatrick scored 2 goals to lead host 
Pacifica (4-1-1, 2-0). Noelle Rost, Kara Jewett, April Burton and Karen 
Wleklinski also scored for Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
St. Margaret's 14, Brethren 0 -- Shelley Lyons and Rachael Frugard scored 4 
goals each for host St. Margaret's (1-5-2, 1-2-2), which set a single-game 
school record for goals. Wendy Brown and Ashley Wacholder each scored twice and 
Lisa Frisco added a goal for St. Margaret's. Brethren kicked the ball into its 
net for the final goal. 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 2, Orange Lutheran 0 -- Suzanne Brown scored a goal in each 
half for host Whittier Christian (4-8, 2-3). Orange Lutheran is 2-7-1, 0-4-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 1, Anaheim 0 -- Kristina Yoseloff scored late in the second half for 
host Valencia (4-4-1, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Orange 2, Laguna Beach 0 -- Stacy Long and Debbie Ford scored for visiting 
Orange (6-0-2, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 2, Laguna Hills 1 -- Tina Hall scored the game-winning goal off a 
corner kick with 3 minutes to play for the Warriors at home. Suzie Baldwin also 
scored for Woodbridge (6-7-1 overall, 1-0 in league). Laya Dogmetchie had 4 
saves in the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly Besser scored 10 minutes into the second half for Laguna Hills (0-1 in 
league). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 1, Newport Harbor 0 -- Prentice Perkins scored with 5 minutes 
left for host Corona del Mar (9-5-2, 1-1). Kim Kolstat had 4 saves for Corona 
del Mar. Newport Harbor is 5-6, 0-2. 
</P>
<P>
University 9, Saddleback 0 -- Inge Haskins, Sandra Brishka and Julie Simpson 
each scored twice and Shana Novegrod, Liz Dale and Stacy McGinley each had one 
goal to lead host University (6-6-0, 2-0). Saddleback (0-2) did not have a shot 
on goal. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills 2, San Clemente 0 -- Megan Fosberg scored 2 goals in the first 15 
minutes for Dana Hills (12-2-4, 2-0-1). San is 6-7-2, 1-2-0. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
Marina 1, Edison 0 -- Melanie Frakes scored late in the second half for host 
Marina (9-5-2, 3-0-1), which was tied for first with Edison (8-6-1, 2-1-1) 
going into the match. 
</P>
