<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRESNO ST. WOMEN END FULLERTON STREAK AT 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fresno State stopped Cal State Fullerton's 10-game winning streak Thursday with 
a 66-46 victory in a Big West Conference women's basketball team Thursday at 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton shot 26% (7 of 27) in the first half as Fresno opened a 33-16 lead. 
Things didn't get any better for the Titans in the second half when they shot 
25% (8 of 32). 
</P>
<P>
Yvette Roberts scored a game-high 23 points and Simone Srubek added 14 for 
Fresno (11-4 overall and 2-2 in conference play). Felicia Benson scored 14 and 
Gena Miller had 10 for Fullerton (11-2, 3-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
