<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
January appears to be a big month for consummating deals. Among the bigger ones 
announced recently: Irvine developer O'Donnell, Armstrong &amp; Partners bought 
131 acres in Rancho Cucamonga for $15 million with the Boston Co., a 
Massachusetts pension fund adviser, and plans to build 2.5 million square feet 
of factories and warehouses. Construction on the land -- next to a similar 
O'Donnell project -- begins in the spring. 
</P>
<P>
Erin Mason Ltd. Inc. of Newport Beach bought 300 acres in Riverside and San 
Bernardino counties from Ahmanson Commercial Development Corp. of Los Angeles 
for $18.5 million. Erin Mason said it would build roads and other amenities and 
sell lots to heavy industry. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick F. Cadigan of Newport Beach bought Monterey Pines Apartments in Tustin 
for $13.7 million from Balcor Realty Co. of Skokie, Ill. Located on Williams 
Street, the complex has 224 units. 
</P>
<P>
And the Coopers &amp; Lybrand accounting firm signed a $7.9-million lease for 
28,000 square feet of office space at 4675 MacArthur Court in Newport Beach, an 
Irvine Co. building. Coldwell Banker represented the landlord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
